  "prompt": "Can one change branch from biotechnology engineering to engineering physics in IIT Roorkee?",
  "response": "Changing branches at IIT Roorkee, or any IIT, is typically subject to certain conditions and policies set by the institute. Generally, the ability to change branches depends on factors such as:\n\n1. **Academic Performance**: You usually need to have a high CPI (Cumulative Performance Index) or GPA (Grade Point Average) in your first year. Top-performing students may have the option to apply for a branch change.\n\n2. **Availability of Seats**: The transfer is subject to the availability of seats in the desired branch. If the branch you want to transfer to does not have any vacancies, it might not be possible to make the change.\n\n3. **Institute-specific Rules**: Each IIT may have specific guidelines and criteria for branch change, which can include a cap on the number of students allowed to transfer and specific application procedures.\n\nTo get accurate and detailed information:\n- **Consult the Institute\u2019s Academic Office**: The academic office can provide the most current and comprehensive details regarding the process, eligibility, and deadlines for branch change.\n- **Refer to the Academic Curriculum Rules**: Check the student handbook and academic regulations published by IIT Roorkee for any specific criteria.\n\nIf you are a current undergraduate student at IIT Roorkee, reaching out directly to your academic advisor or the administration would be the best course of action for personalized advice.",
